dismissalComment.html: big appeal and given. Munro had been flirting with danger, shuffling across and trying to play through the leg side, this time it nipped back into him and given the relative lack of bounce, struck on the knee roll, caught plumb in front

dismissalText.long: c Tamim Iqbal b Mohammad Saifuddin
dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill c Tamim Iqbal b Mohammad Saifuddin 29 (40b 3x4 1x6 51m) SR: 72.5

dismissalComment.html: taken brilliantly at long-on and Guptill won't be the first from his country to get three hundreds in a bilateral series. It was full on off, Guptill picked him up down the ground, perhaps meant to go slightly straighter, but the fielder judged it beautifully, first taking it and then as he overbalanced, had the presence of mind to toss it up back into play and catch it again while he was in the air, before coming back into playing area

dismissalComment.html: and he strikes first ball! Back of a length on off, and he tries to drag a pull. Bat's face turns in his hand, and he slices the shot in the air. No mistake from midwicket

edged and taken! Full on off, and angling further away from the batsman. But Tamim's in no mood to hang around. Skips down the ground and try to slash a shot over cover. Finds the thick outside edge to the keeper instead

middle stump rocked back! Great swing bowling on display. Full on off, and swinging inwards sharply. Ball jags back after hitting the deck, and Sarkar has driven down the wrong line. Stumps rattled and Southee has his second!

commentTextItems.html: that's six for Southee! Length ball on off, and Sabbir looks to pull. Bat flies out of his hand while playing that shot, while the lobbed chance is taken by Southee running forward. New Zealand win by 88 runs

commentPostTextItems.html: 7pm That's all from us at Dunedin. Hope you enjoyed our coverage of the ODI series. See you soon for the Test series. Till then, on behalf of Ankur Dhawan and Ranjith P, this is Sreshth Shah signing off.
6.50pm We should have the captains' reactions and the trophy presentation now.
Mashrafe, the losing captain: "Boys are disappointed, but Sabbir's ton was a positive. Today's match was alright for 35 overs (in NZ's innings) but after Neesham's knock it was tough."
Martin Guptill, the Man of the Series: "Nice to come back after an injury break. Been working on a couple of balance things. Will do the same before going into the Plunket Shield."

Tim Southee, the Man of the Match: "It was nice, been working on a few things - nice to do it in the middle and contribute to a team win. Just working on to get a few things right. The one-day game has been a bit off, so I've been hitting the deck harder and getting some swing. There's some great competition among the fast bowlers, we are good mates and are pushing each other. Healthy competition. The batting display today was great. Guys who didn't bat a lot in this series got a go today. Looking forward to the Tests, always good to put on the whites."

Bpagur: "BD was consistent, in both good (230+ runs) and bad (failed top order) terms. I hope tigers would go back to the whiteboard and take the lesson learned from this series. We missed Saki bal hasan, hope he will be back soon. Thank you cricinfo."

6.45pm Sabbir the last man to go, and he should walk back proud. But only if he had some support, this game could've gone a completely different way. Southee the star with the ball, while three half-centuries from New Zealand in the first innings will keep them happy going into the World Cup.
Saad: "So our capacity is 250 in a bouncy track against swing bowling and probably we will play in similar tracks in the World Cup against many of the similar attacks. "
Naim Noor Arnob: "6 for Southee means he will start before Henry in the World Cup, right?" -- he's definitely made his case
Vinod Rajpal: "@Sreshth Shah; are u following Oman vs Scotland ODI ?" -- yep, Oman are 32 for no loss already, eight runs better than their show last evening
safwan: "The partnerships required at the beginning came at the end. BD really need to focus. Hope to see some positive cricket in World Cup"
Gaurav Varyani: "Sixer Southee has taken six...."

length ball, just outside off, and he tries to drive. Slices the shot over point, and enough time to come back for the second run
full and wide outside off, and he sticks his bat out. Ball hits his blade and pings away towards point

commentPostTextItems.html: Rafi Ullah: "Personal achievement also counts for team, Shabbir have taken the total to a respectable position & reduced margin of defeat"

commentTextItems.html: full on off stump, and he drills this drive to wide long-off. Just the single though

commentPreTextItems.html: That was Southee's first five-wicket haul since his five-for against England at World Cup 2015

commentTextItems.html: back of a length on middle, and he lets it go through to the keeper
full on middle, and whipped away to midwicket. Straight to the fielder though

commentPostTextItems.html: Faizan Khan: "Why all the impetus is always on Tamim or Shakib to score. younger players have to raise their game standard."

commentTextItems.html: full on off, and worked off his toes to backward square. They jog across for one

commentPostTextItems.html: James: "Just a 4 off every ball to win..."

commentPostTextItems.html: Baundule: "Don't like the extravagant celebration of Shabbir after the century. It shows the priority is his personal achievement, not the team's win."

commentTextItems.html: back of a length on off, and the ball goes over his shoulder to the keeper

commentPostTextItems.html: Hamza Shah: "What if tamim had scored today, BD could have won this match easily due to superb century of sabir" -- Or Liton, Soumya or Mushfiqur

commentTextItems.html: back of a length on off, and he top-edges this over Latham's head for four! Mehidy won't mind

hundred for Sabbir! Pulls this length ball to backward square to get there. Fistpumps while running to the other end, then does the sajdeh to wrap up his celebrations. Then raises his bat, and does a 'mouth' sign with his hands. Something for his critics, perhaps
full just outside off, and he pierces the gap for a beautiful cover drive! Moves on to 99, just one away from his maiden ODI ton
back of a length on off, and he attempts to pull. Top-edged beyond midwicket, but lands safe with two players running in
yorker just outside off, and he fails to connect with the drive. Toe-ends the shot
full and wide outside off, and driven away from his body to deep extra cover

commentPostTextItems.html: Imam: "While Saifuddin is improving very fast and seems to have more resolve than some of his other colleagues, he is not good enough to be in the XI. He is a good no. 8 batsman and a very good no. 6 bowler. Bits and pieces allrounders do not work any more. However, hopefully he will continue to improve. "

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal c †Latham b Southee 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: edged and taken! Full on off, and angling further away from the batsman. But Tamim's in no mood to hang around. Skips down the ground and try to slash a shot over cover. Finds the thick outside edge to the keeper instead

headshotImage.longCaption: Liton Das player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Litton Das lbw b Southee 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: appeal for lbw, and given! Liton wants to review, but the umpire says he's too late to decide. Full ball drifting into leg stump. Liton misses the clip, ball stays low and hits his front leg. No hesitation from the umpire to raise his finger. Southee has his third!

dismissalText.commentary: Soumya Sarkar b Southee 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: middle stump rocked back! Great swing bowling on display. Full on off, and swinging inwards sharply. Ball jags back after hitting the deck, and Sarkar has driven down the wrong line. Stumps rattled and Southee has his second!

headshotImage.caption: Colin Munro player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Colin Munro player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Munro b Boult 17 (27b 3x4 0x6 47m) SR: 62.96

dismissalComment.html: taken at third man! Length ball on middle, and Mushi tries to flick this away to square leg. Takes a top-edge, and the ball has a lot of hang time. Allows Munro to compose himself near the boundary, and his bucket-hands make no mistake

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah c Munro b de Grandhomme 16 (36b 1x4 1x6 57m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: straight to deep square leg! Length ball on middle, and Mahmudullah backs away to make some room. Slogs towards deep midwicket, but he toe-ends the shot, and Munro takes another skyer

dismissalText.commentary: Sabbir Rahman c & b Southee 102 (110b 12x4 2x6 158m) SR: 92.72

dismissalComment.html: that's six for Southee! Length ball on off, and Sabbir looks to pull. Bat flies out of his hand while playing that shot, while the lobbed chance is taken by Southee running forward. New Zealand win by 88 runs

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Saifuddin c Guptill b Boult 44 (63b 4x4 0x6 79m) SR: 69.84

dismissalComment.html: and he strikes first ball! Back of a length on off, and he tries to drag a pull. Bat's face turns in his hand, and he slices the shot in the air. No mistake from midwicket

dismissalText.commentary: Mashrafe Mortaza c Boult b Southee 2 (3b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Number four for Southee! Short again, and Mashrafe tries to muscle this over backward square leg. Top-edges it to fine leg where Boult does well to hang on to the catch. Checks his feet, and they're nowhere near the boundary. The Bangladesh captain makes his way back

dismissalComment.html: full and wide outside off, and he tries to muscle a drive. Slices the shot, and Guptill takes a stunner to earn Southee his five-wicket haul! Guptill runs from point towards the boundary, and with the ball going away, he dives full-stretch to take a screamer. Mehidy goes for an entertaining 37
